  "prompt": "Is there something that Sachin Tendulkar has not done in cricket?",
  "response": "Sachin Tendulkar, often regarded as one of the greatest cricketers of all time, has had an extraordinary career with numerous records and achievements. However, there are a few things he has not accomplished in cricket, including:\n\n1. **World Cup Victory as Captain**: While Tendulkar played in six Cricket World Cups and was part of the Indian team that won the tournament in 1983 and 2011, he never captained India to a World Cup victory.\n\n2. **T20 International World Cup Win**: Tendulkar did not play in the T20 format during the ICC T20 World Cup era as a player, as he announced his retirement from international T20 cricket before the inaugural T20 World Cup in 2007.\n\n3. **Test Match Captaincy Longevity**: Although he captained the Indian Test team on various occasions, he did not have a long or highly successful tenure as captain compared to other greats in cricket.\n\n4. **Playing in the IPL**: The Indian Premier League (IPL) began in 2008, after Tendulkar had already been established as a legend of the game, and while he did participate in the IPL, it was towards the end of his career.\n\n5. **100 Test Matches as Captain**: While he played over 200 Tests, he did not accumulate 100 matches as a captain.\n\nDespite these omissions, Tendulkar's illustrious career includes many unparalleled accomplishments, making him a cricketing icon.",
